Text.Value: Now leave. I will feed alone.
I will not let you feed on anything in this city, aberration.
I'm not going to bring you food.
*You try to pick your way silently through the loose rocks and broken masonry, but to no avail.*
WAKE UP, SQUIDFACE!
You have done me a service and received appropriate thanks.
I sense you are under-developed. Bring me a brain and I will help you augment yourself.
Be quick. Time is on no one's side.
Return with the one you follow - I will speak to them and no other.
I cannot risk this body. I have heard the call - we will all be needed for what is to come.
Very well, kin, I shall dine on you.
I can still taste his terror. It is delicious, but will not sustain me.
This one is newly changed. Its body is weak, its potential ripe for harvesting.
Ah, you again. I have all I need, I require neither your services nor your master's.
Leave.
But I require an equal. Return with the one you follow. I shall speak with them.
I never work for free.
Go find your own meal! Even weakened you're more powerful than anything out there.
You would betray us? Then you shall be our very first meal.
You are an ally of my people. A servant, perhaps?
*Before you lies the unconscious body of a mind flayer, glistening and raw.*
You are like me - like I was - a vessel, yet to transform.
A newborn? Unattended? How fortunate.
...what are you? What am I sensing?
My vessel. He fought the transformation - he found it excoriating.
Not yet - I just need a little more time.
Offer the mind flayer the body you're carrying.
Leave.
You return. Will you aid me?
But no matter, I desire solitude. Leave me.
It doesn't feel very fortunate.
Offer the mind flayer the body you're carrying.
Curtail your sympathy. We wish to destroy the elder brain, not nourish its thralls.
Go on. Kill it. Absorb its power.
I can fetch you a corpse, freshly killed. Brain intact.
Help me. You must.
You are correct. I am ready.
Just like you did before.
You approach me again. And again I tell you, I require someone blessed with an illithid passenger.
*You feel its presence gently probing the palace of your mind. As it finds a mostly-vacant spot, power and knowledge flood your brain, unlocking a new secret.*
Oh but it is. This one has only just transformed. It is weak, vulnerable - its potential ripe for harvesting.
Will you help me? I am still weak after my transformation. Still hungry.
Ally, then. 'Friend'.
What do you need?
You return. You look stronger as I grow only weaker.
We need to feed. We need a brain, fresh and frantic, to restore our strength.
Connect your mind to this fledgling aberration - wake it up.
Wake the newborn mind flayer.
Attack!
I require an equal: one with the same power flowing through their form.
Who is there? Who shall be my first meal?
Just like you did before.
Help me. I am so hungry.
Come no closer, you - you...

EditorData.NodeContext: Saying "come no closer, you wretch!" but stalls on 'you' because it realises you're not what it thought you were

Text.Value: Sneak away.
I shall be here, waiting for your return.
Show this aberration what you really serve - end its sorry existence.
Attack.
This abomination's existence pollutes the very air - try to end it.
Attack the creature before it wakes up.
Insolent lackey! You will be my very first meal.
Yes, that will do nicely.
Be swift kin. I need your aid.
Call it what you will - we are all threads in the fabric of the Grand Design.
Leave.
Was it you I heard screaming when I entered the windmill?
Go on. Kill it. Absorb its power.
We are new to our collective. Our - my birth was difficult. The vessel fought hard. It left me weak.
Just like you did before.
*You pick your way silently through the loose rocks and broken masonry until you're a safe distance away.*
Go on. Kill it. Absorb its power.
Why am I being disturbed?

EditorData.logicalname: GAVE BODY TO MF - NOT MET

Text.Value: Attack!
So loud... Why are you - you...

EditorData.NodeContext: saying "why are you shouting" but stalls on the "you" as it realised the player is something different, strange

Text.Value: I'm no one's servant.
Take this. I have no use for such baubles now. It may aid you.
What are you doing here?
What? No - I've had so little time!
Ah, the trace of illithid power. There is none in your body, but you have been close to it. Touched by it.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The sleeping mind flayer wakes up and stands up

Text.Value: A newborn. Vulnerable, its potential ripe for harvesting.
And as you have aided me, so I shall aid you.
You have returned. With a meal, I hope.
I'll see what I can do.

Synopsis:
Windmill mindflayer asks player to bring it a corpse to feed on.
Speaker 3 is an optional non-illithid player that will briefly be pointed out as potential food in the conversation.
